            "description": {
                "content": "OpenAPI specification for candidate registration, mobile/email OTP verification, CAPTCHA login, draft-based multi-step application form, document upload, payment verification, final submission, dashboard status, and print preview.\n\nHTTP Status Code Standard applied in this specification:\n- 200 OK: successful read/update/action response.\n- 201 Created: candidate registration, document upload, and payment order creation.\n- 400 Bad Request: malformed request, missing required body, invalid path/query/body format.\n- 401 Unauthorized: missing/expired token, invalid credentials, invalid OTP/token where applicable.\n- 403 Forbidden: valid identity but action is not allowed for candidate/resource state.\n- 404 Not Found: requested candidate/application/document/payment resource does not exist.\n- 409 Conflict: duplicate record, already submitted application, already verified OTP, or state conflict.\n- 422 Unprocessable Entity: business validation failed with field-level errors.\n- 429 Too Many Requests: rate limit exceeded.\n- 500 Internal Server Error: unexpected backend failure.\n\n\nContact Support:\n Name: Frontend Requirement Specification",
                "type": "text/plain"
            }
        }
